es.upv.grc.grcbox.common

Class GrcBoxRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.upv.grc.grcbox.common.GrcBoxRule

  • public class GrcBoxRule
extends java.lang.Object
    The Class GrcBoxRule. This class represents a GRCBox rule GRCBox rules directly maps to Iptables rules Currently only TCP and UDP protocols are supported.

      • GrcBoxRule

        public GrcBoxRule(int id,
                  GrcBoxRule.Protocol proto,
                  GrcBoxRule.RuleType type,
                  int appid,
                  java.lang.String ifName,

                  int srcPort,
                  int dstPort,
                  java.lang.String srcAddr,
                  java.lang.String dstAddr,
                  int dstFwdPort,
                  java.lang.String dstFwdAddr)
        Instantiates a new grc box rule.
        Parameters:
        id - the id, this value is ignored when registering a rules on the server
        proto - the proto
        type - the type
        appid - the appid
        ifName - the interface name
        expireDate - the expire date
        srcPort - the source port, if -1 any port is used
        dstPort - the destination port, if -1 any port is used
        srcAddr - the source address, if null any address is used
        dstAddr - the destination address
        dstFwdPort - the destination forwarding port, is ignored for outgoing rules, must be defined for incoming rules
        dstFwdAddr - the destination forwarding address, is ignored for outgoing rules, must be defined for incoming rules

      • GrcBoxRule

        public GrcBoxRule(int id,
                  GrcBoxRule.Protocol proto,
                  GrcBoxRule.RuleType type,
                  int appid,
                  java.lang.String ifName,
                  long expireDate,

                  int dstFwdPort,
                  java.lang.String dstFwdAddr,
                  java.lang.String mcastPlugin)
        Instantiates a new grc box rule.
        Parameters:
        id - the id, this value is ignored when registering a rules on the server
        proto - the proto
        type - the type
        appid - the appid
        ifName - the interface name
        expireDate - the expire date
        srcPort - the source port, if -1 any port is used
        dstPort - the destination port, if -1 any port is used
        srcAddr - the source address, if null any address is used
        dstAddr - the destination address
        dstFwdPort - the destination forwarding port, is ignored for outgoing rules, must be defined for incoming rules
        dstFwdAddr - the destination forwarding address, is ignored for outgoing rules, must be defined for incoming rules
        mcastPlugin - the multicast plugin. A list of valid multicast plugins must be obtained from the server
